result.formatted_address: 1-11 Mallory St, Wan Chai, Hong Kong
result.name: Queen's Cafe

reviews.text: Staff were nice and friendly and accommodating.  Did was unique and great!
Lunch is good,  Price acceptable
Good atmosphere, food OK, and extremely reasonable, portion is big, service is wonderful. Highly recommend for lunch

A great venue, in a unique space for Hong Kong – especially Hong Kong Island and the heart of Wanchai, where you are surrounded by a warm retro decor with light jazz playing in the background, it really is a great place to sit down and enjoy lunch with a friend or two, the staff, although not overly friendly, were swift and professional in their interactions and service. However, in spite of the outward persona, I was not offered an ala carte menu by the manager on duty, I was only given the set-lunch-menu and told that it was lunchtime! Unfortunately, The food [provided on the set-lunch-menu] could only be described as functional; it certainly wasn’t befitting such a wonderful space. It was only upon paying and departing that I noticed another table ordering from an ala carte menu, which upset me as I felt that the quality of the food [from the set-menu] let the restaurant down and, I would much have preferred to have ordered a light meal from the ala carte menu. I would go back – simply because of the proximity to my office and the convenience of its location, however, having being railroaded once – into buying a T-Bone Steak what could only be described as a chewy shoe insole – I won't make the same mistake twice. My recommendation is that you ignore the set-menu and insist on the ala carte menu.
Food was ok, plates are HK style western food. Crowded during weekday lunch time.

reviews.text: A quite, relaxing vintage restaurant in a preserved heritage building serving delicious Hong Kong-style western dishes.
Nice atmosphere serving western restaurant menu. Take reservation.
Good and quiet place for afternoon high tea. Friendly staff. Located in a Class 3 historical building.
If you are craving some old school goulash or chicken stroganoff
Disappoint services. Miss our order and required us to wait for a while. No apology at all. Not recommend to go during rush hour

result.adr_address: 香港灣仔茂蘿街1-11
result.name: 皇后飯店 Queen's Cafe

reviews.text: 甜品不錯，不仿一嘗
A quite, relaxing vintage restaurant in a preserved heritage building serving delicious Hong Kong-style western dishes.
餐廳在一幢改建的舊樓，冇乜明確嘅指示，較難搵到， 餐廳裝修懷舊典雅值得一讚， 打卡一流， 但食物一般， 我order的燒牛肉沙律，沙律份量太大堆頭不夠精緻，牛肉冇味， 比較失望， 而咖啡給我的感覺只有一個字……濃
串燒牛柳餐，牛柳很好食
食品可以，環境燈光過幽暗，食飽後有啲想瞓覺

result.adr_address: 香港灣仔茂蘿街1-11號
result.name: Queen's Cafe

reviews.text:
食物方面份量很多及味道不錯，如果想吃一個悠閒的午餐可以選擇到這裏，因為他基本上中午之後的時間都沒太多人，也不用等位
價位來港大約一百元多點一個午餐， 下午茶相對較貴，一個炸雞髀配薯條或吃一個湯烏冬下午茶就要80多元， 差不多 酒店給的價錢
但如果兩個人想悠閒地享受寧靜或談天說地多個小時，這個不失為一個很好的地方~
Staff were nice and friendly and accommodating.  Did was unique and great!
Lunch is good,  Price acceptable
午餐不錯，但人手不足。
環境好，食物正常
